svg.metadata: Created by FontForge 20170924 at Tue Mar 13 20:17:45 2012 By www-data Nitti is a monospaced typeface family in five weights that has its roots in the first sans-serif designs of the 19th century the Grotesques. Originally a British invention, the Grotesques gained massive popularity in mainland Europe and also became widespread in early 20th century USA where it was commonly referred to as O^GothicO~. The quirky and often idiosyncratic shapes of these designs lend them a humanity and warmth which is still appreciated among many graphic designers. E^ Nitti is named after Francesco Raffaele Nitto, better known as Frank 'The Enforcer' Nitti, one of the henchmen of Al Capone. The typeface family is part of a bigger collection of Grotesque-inspired typefaces that also includes a poster version called 'Stanley' and a proportional version called 'Erminio'.
